id: pm-dyzy
title: "PR #406 review follow-up: clear partial MCP extension registries before fallback execution"
description: "Follow-up from CodeRabbit on PR #406 under pm-zumn. If a setActive* publish call throws after earlier process-global extension registries were set, withActiveExtensionsExclusively currently falls back to run(active=null) before the finally clears those partially published globals. Fix by resetting the active extension registries immediately in the catch path before fallback execution, and reuse the same reset logic in final teardown so built-in fallback actions observe a clean inactive registry."
type: Chore
status: closed
priority: 2
tags[4]: "area:extensions","area:mcp",pm-cli,review-followup
created_at: "2026-06-30T08:03:03.421Z"
updated_at: "2026-06-30T08:40:54.137Z"
author: claude-code-agent
parent: pm-zumn
resolution: "Added resetActiveExtensionRegistries() and invoked it in the activation catch path before run(active=null), with final teardown using the same reset helper; consumed pm-changelog 2026.6.30 via project install."
expected_result: "If any active-extension registry publish step throws, fallback built-in MCP actions run with empty active registries and no partially published extension state; changelog generation remains current with the latest pm-changelog package."
actual_result: Fallback execution now observes empty hook/command/parser/preflight/service/renderer/registration registries before run(active=null); targeted regression and full gates passed; temp-dir smoke with pm-changelog 2026.6.30 passed.
